    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A vertical column of divine fire roars down from the heavens in a location you specify. Each creature in a 10-foot-radius, 40-foot-high cylinder centered on a point within range must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes [[/damage 4d6 type=fire]] damage and [[/damage 4d6 type=radiant]] damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p></p><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"At Higher Levels\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the fire damage or the radiant damage (your choice) increases by [[/damage 1d6]] for each slot level above 5th.</p></div></div>",
